Magic Software Advances Most in Three Weeks as Profit Jumps 84%

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-08-03T08:57:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/magic-software-advances-most-in-three-weeks-as-profit-jumps-84-.html
Magic Software Enterprises Ltd. (MGIC) 
gained the most in more than three weeks after the Israeli
software developer said second-quarter net income soared 84
percent to $3.55 million.  The shares increased 6.6 percent, the most since July 10,
to 19.30 shekels at 11:43 a.m. in  Tel Aviv , giving the Or
Yehuda, Israel-based company a market value of 710 million
shekels ($205 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  